{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Camera"], "type": "title", "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "text": ["You can view your scene through a camera, and render from its point\nof view."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The left menu chooses the order in which transforms are applied\n    (for example, scale, then rotate, then translate). This can change the\n    position and orientation of the object, in the same way that going a\n    block and turning east takes you to a different place than turning east\n    and then going a block."]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The right menu chooses the order in which to rotate around the\n    X, Y, and Z axes. Certain orders can make character joint\n    transforms easier to use, depending on the character."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Transform Order"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "xord"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Translation along XYZ axes."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Translate"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "t"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Degrees rotation about XYZ axes."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Rotate"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "r"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Local origin of the object.\n    See also ", {"_hs_sc": true, "text": ["setting the pivot point"], "value": "/basics/objects", "fullpath": "/basics/objects", "scheme": null, "type": "link"}, " ."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Pivot"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "p"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["This menu contains options for manipulating the\n    ", {"_hs_sc": true, "fragment": "#pretransform", "text": ["pre-transform"], "value": "/basics/objects#pretransform", "fullpath": "/basics/objects#pretransform", "scheme": null, "type": "link"}, " values. The pre-transform is an internal\n    transform that is applied prior to the regular transform parameters.\n    This allows you to change the frame of reference for the translate, rotate,\n    scale parameter values below without changing the overall transform."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This reverts the translate, rotate, scale parameters to their\n        default values while maintaining the same overall transform."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Clean Transform"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This sets the translate parameter to (0, 0, 0) while maintaining\n        the same overall transform."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Clean Translates"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This sets the rotate parameter to (0, 0, 0) while maintaining the\n        same overall transform."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Clean Rotates"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This sets the scale parameter to (1, 1, 1) while maintaining the\n        same overall transform."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Clean Scales"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This removes the pre-transform by setting the translate, rotate,\n        and scale parameters in order to maintain the same overall\n        transform. Note that if there were shears in the pre-transform, it can not be completely removed."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Extract Pre-transform"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This completely removes the pre-transform without changing any\n        parameters. This will change the overall transform of the object if\n        there are any non-default values in the translate, rotate, and\n        scale parameters."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Reset Pre-transform"]}], "type": "dt_group", "container": true}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Modify Pre-Transform"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "pretransform"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When the object is re-parented, maintain its current world position by\n    changing the object\u2019s transform parameters."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Keep Position When Parenting"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "keeppos"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["When the object is being transformed, maintain the current world transforms \n    of its children by changing their transform parameters."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Child Compensation"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "childcomp"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Enable ", {"text": ["Constraints Network"], "type": "ui"}, " on the object."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Enable Constraints"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "constraints_on"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Path to a CHOP ", {"text": ["Constraints Network"], "type": "ui"}, ".\n    See also ", {"_hs_sc": true, "text": ["creating constraints"], "value": "/character/constraints", "fullpath": "/character/constraints", "scheme": null, "type": "link"}, "."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["You can you use the Constraints drop down button to activate one of the Constraints Shelf Tool. If you do so, the first pick session is filled automatically by nodes selected in the parameter panel."]}], "role": "item", "indent": 4, "type": "tip"}], "role": "item_group", "container": true, "type": "tip_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Lookat and Follow Path parameters on object nodes are deprecated in favor of ", {"_hs_sc": true, "text": ["Look At"], "value": "/shelf/constraintlookat", "fullpath": "/shelf/constraintlookat", "scheme": null, "type": "link"}, " and ", {"_hs_sc": true, "text": ["Follow Path"], "value": "/shelf/constraintpath", "fullpath": "/shelf/constraintpath", "scheme": null, "type": "link"}, " constraints.\n        The parameters are only hidden for now and you can set their visibitily if you do edit the node\u2019s parameter interface."]}], "role": "item", "indent": 4, "type": "note"}], "role": "item_group", "container": true, "type": "note_group"}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Constraints"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "constraints_path"}, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Transform"], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Whether or not this object is displayed in the viewport and rendered.\n    Turn on the checkbox to have Houdini use this parameter,\n    then set the value to 0 to hide the object in the viewport and not render it,\n    or 1 to show and render the object.\n    If the checkbox is off, Houdini ignores the value."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Display"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "display"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Use the specified wireframe color"]}], "type": "parameters_item", "role": "item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Set Wireframe Color"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The display color of the object"]}], "type": "parameters_item", "role": "item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Wireframe Color"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Object is capable of being picked in the viewport."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Viewport Selecting Enabled"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "picking"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Script to run when the object is picked in the viewport. See\n    ", {"_hs_sc": true, "text": ["select scripts"], "value": "/commands/_guide", "fullpath": "/commands/_guide", "scheme": null, "type": "link"}, " ."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Select Script"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "pickscript"}, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["Caches object transforms once Houdini calculates them. This is\n    especially useful for objects whose world space position is\n    expensive to calculate (such as ", {"_hs_sc": true, "text": ["Sticky objects"], "value": "/nodes/obj/sticky", "fullpath": "/nodes/obj/sticky", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link"}, "),\n    and objects at the end of long parenting chains (such as\n    ", {"_hs_sc": true, "text": ["Bones"], "value": "/nodes/obj/bone", "fullpath": "/nodes/obj/bone", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link"}, "). This option is turned on by default for Sticky and\n    Bone objects."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["See the ", {"text": ["OBJ Caching"], "type": "ui"}, " section of the\n    ", {"_hs_sc": true, "fragment": "#objcache", "text": ["Houdini Preferences"], "value": "/ref/windows/mainprefs#objcache", "fullpath": "/ref/windows/mainprefs#objcache", "scheme": null, "type": "link"}, " window\n    for how to control the size of the object transform cache."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Cache Object Transform"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "cachedata"}, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Render"], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Scales the viewport geometry. This parameter is only for display\n    purposes."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Icon scale"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "iconscale"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "iconscale"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The output resolution in pixels. Standard presets are available via the pull down menu to the right of the parameter."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Resolution"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "res"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "res"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The pixel aspect ratio of the output image."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Pixel aspect ratio"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"ifdprop": "image:pixelaspect", "hprop": "aspect"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "aspect"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Type of camera projection used for rendering (for example, perspective or orthographic)."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This simulates the classic pinhole camera where camera rays emanate\n        from a common camera origin through a flat camera plane."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Perspective"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This uses parallel camera rays that are orthogonal to the (flat)\n        camera plane. The width of the view volume is determined by the\n        Ortho Width parameter below."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Orthographic"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This projection uses a spherical camera plane for rendering."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Polar (panoramic)"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["This projection uses a cylindrical camera plane for rendering."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Cylindrical (panoramic)"]}], "type": "dt_group", "container": true}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Lens Shader:\n    Use a lens shader to initialize rays for ray tracing."]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Selecting ", {"text": ["Polar"], "type": "ui"}, ", ", {"text": ["Cylindrical"], "type": "ui"}, " or ", {"text": ["Lens Shader"], "type": "ui"}, " will automatically switch the ", {"text": ["Rendering Engine"], "type": "ui"}, " (on the output driver) to ", {"text": ["Ray Tracing"], "type": "ui"}, ", as it is impossible to render these projections with micropolygon rendering."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Projection"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "projection"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "projection"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Camera focal length (zoom)."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Focal length"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "focal"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "focal"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The units used for the focal length."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Focal units"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "focalunits"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "focalunits"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Width of the visible field."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 12, "text": ["The correct aperture width for Super 35mm format motion picture film is 24.89."]}], "role": "item", "indent": 8, "type": "note"}], "role": "item_group", "container": true, "type": "note_group"}], "role": "item", "text": [{"_hs_sc": true, "text": "", "value": "/nodes/images/fov.png", "fullpath": "/nodes/images/fov.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link"}], "indent": 4, "type": "fig"}], "role": "item_group", "container": true, "type": "fig_group"}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Aperture"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "aperture"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "aperture"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Width of orthographic view volume when using Projection is set to\n    Orthographic."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Otho width"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"ifdprop": "camera:orthowidth", "hprop": "orthowidth"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "orthowidth"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Position of near clipping plane."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Near clipping"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "near"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "near"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Position of far clipping plane."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Far clipping"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "far"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "far"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Define the center of the window during the rendering process."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Screen window X/Y"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "win"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "win"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Scale for expanding the cropped area specified by the ", {"text": ["Crop"], "type": "ui"}, " parameters."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Screen window size"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "winsize"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "winsize"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Sets the screen window mask to cover the bounding box of the selected object(s)."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Screen window mask"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "winmask"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "winmask"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Left cropping margin for camera\u2019s view area."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Left crop"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "cropl"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "cropl"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Right cropping margin for camera\u2019s view area."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Right crop"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "cropr"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "cropr"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Bottom cropping margin for camera\u2019s view area."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Bottom crop"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "cropb"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "cropb"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Top cropping margin for camera\u2019s view area."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Top crop"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "cropt"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "cropt"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Sets the pixel crop region to cover the bounding box of the selected object(s)."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Crop Mask"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "cropmask"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "cropmask"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["You can optionally add the spare parameter ", {"text": ["Visible Objects"], "type": "ui"}, " from the Parameter Interface. This allows you to control which objects are displayed in the viewport when looking through the camera."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "note"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["View"], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The portion of the frame interval that the camera shutter is\n    open. Used to determine motion blur. ", {"text": ["[0,1]"], "type": "code"}]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Shutter time"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"hprop": "shutter"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "shutter"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The lens focal distance and distance from the camera at\n    which objects will be in focus. This is only used when rendering using depth of field. Objects outside this distance will be blurred."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Focus distance"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"ifdprop": "camera:focus", "hprop": "focus"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "focus"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Lens fstop. This is only used when rendering using depth of field.\n    Determines blurriness of depth of field effects."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["F-stop"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"ifdprop": "camera:fstop", "hprop": "fstop"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "fstop"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Filter kernel used in depth of field rendering. Use the pop-up menu to the right of the text box to choose from the available options."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Use a gaussian filter kernel (highest quality)."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Radial bokeh (", {"text": ["radial"], "type": "code"}, ")"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Use an image file "]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Image file bokeh (", {"text": ["file"], "type": "code"}, ")"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Use a box filter kernal."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Box filter bokeh (", {"text": ["box"], "type": "code"}, ")"]}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Do not filter."]}], "type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Disable bokeh (", {"text": ["null"], "type": "code"}, ")"]}], "type": "dt_group", "container": true}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Bokeh"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"ifdprop": "camera:bokeh", "hprop": "vm_bokeh"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "vm_bokeh"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The file to use for \"file\" shaped bokeh.  White/black cutout images that delineate the shape of the lens are good candidates, where white regions represent the areas that light passes through."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Bokeh image file"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"ifdprop": "camera:bokeh", "hprop": "vm_bokehfile"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "vm_bokehfile"}, {"body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The rotation for \"file\" shaped bokeh."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Bokeh rotation"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"ifdprop": "camera:bokeh", "hprop": "vm_bokehrotation"}, "type": "parameters_item", "id": "vm_bokehrotation"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "text": ["For information on transforming sub-cameras, see the ", {"_hs_sc": true, "text": ["Stereo Camera Rig help"], "value": "/nodes/obj/stereocamrig", "fullpath": "/nodes/obj/stereocamrig", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Sampling"], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}], "title": ["Camera"], "summary": ["You can view your scene through a camera, and render from its point\nof view."], "attrs": {"version": null, "tags": "cameras", "namespace": null, "internal": "cam", "context": "obj", "type": "node", "icon": "OBJ/camera"}, "included": ["/nodes/obj/common.txt", "/nodes/obj/misc_parms.txt", "/props/_minmax_styles.txt", "/props/mantra.txt", "/shelf/lightsandcameras.txt"], "type": "root"}